        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 10:17PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1017 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coffee Mill Lake, or 11 miles east of Bonham. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Honey Grove, Dodd City, Crockett Lake, Coffee Mill Lake, Windom,
Lannius, Lamasco, Carson, Allens Point, and Allens Chapel.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
